  "props": [
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        2.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "message": "THE POSTMARK\n\nFour pigeon-cotes line the back wall, each named for a village. Letters arrive. Letters depart. The pigeons know their own road.\n\nThe Postmaster keeps the ledger. The Postmaster always has work."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        -1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "COTE: HEARTHOLD\n\nA grey pigeon nestles inside, eyes half-closed. Letters here run east to the village of bakers and Source-priests. Most weeks she carries one or two."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "COTE: BROOKHOLD\n\nA brown pigeon coos softly. The farmstead's letters tend to be longer than the others — there is more to say when there are fields to keep account of."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        -1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": -1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "COTE: OLD HOLD\n\nThis cote is empty. The pigeon used to be silver-grey. The Postmaster keeps the cote ready anyway. 'In case someone writes,' he says."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": -1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "COTE: LIRIEN'S CHAMBER\n\nThe pigeon here is paler than the others, almost white. She comes and goes at her own hours. The Postmaster has never had to feed her. He doesn't ask why."
    },
    {
      "type": "npc",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        0.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "name": "Postmaster Olbrin",
      "body_color": [
        0.55,
        0.5,
        0.45,
        1.0
      ],
      "hat_color": [
        0.4,
        0.55,
        0.42,
        1.0
      ],
      "idle_hint": "[E] Speak with the postmaster",
      "dialog_tree": {
        "start": "root",
        "nodes": {
          "root": {
            "speaker": "Postmaster Olbrin",
            "text": "*he looks up from a tray of small folded letters. The pigeons murmur behind him.*\n\nWalker — letter? News? Or just the smell of the cotes?\n\nWe send to all four. Hearthold, Brookhold, the Old Hold, Lirien's Chamber. The pigeons find their roads.",
            "choices": [
              {"label": "Have you any work for a walker?", "next": "work"},
              {"label": "Tell me about the Old Hold cote.", "next": "old"},
              {"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}
            ]
          },
          "work": {
            "speaker": "Postmaster Olbrin",
            "text": "I do, as it happens. If you walk past one of the four villages, ask if there's a letter waiting to come back to me. Bring it. The pigeons fly the other way; you can fly the way the pigeons don't.\n\nI'll pay in pebbles. Or news. Or both.",
            "choices": [{"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}]
          },
          "old": {
            "speaker": "Postmaster Olbrin",
            "text": "*his voice softens.*\n\nThe last keeper of the Old Hold wrote regularly. Then she didn't. Then she didn't again. I keep the cote ready. The pigeon will come back if there's a letter for her.\n\nSometimes a thing is only a kindness if you do it after it stops mattering.",
            "choices": [{"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}]
          },
          "bye": {
            "speaker": "Postmaster Olbrin",
            "text": "Walk well. Bring me a letter when you next pass a village."
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ],
